# Awesome Soundboard

Self-hosted Next.js soundboard app. Users upload audio clips, organize them into boards, play via hotkeys, and share with private / unlisted / public visibility.

**Repo:** `hackmods/awesome-soundboard` · **Node:** 20+ · **Primary run path:** Docker (`docker compose up --build`)

## Stack

| Layer | Choice |
|-------|--------|
| Framework | Next.js 15 App Router, TypeScript, Tailwind |
| UI | shadcn-style Radix components in `src/components/ui/` |
| Auth | Auth.js v5 (next-auth), email/password, JWT sessions, bcryptjs |
| DB | SQLite via Drizzle ORM + `@libsql/client` (not better-sqlite3) |
| Audio playback | Howler.js — **lazy-import only** (`src/lib/audio/manager.ts`) |
| Waveforms | wavesurfer.js — **lazy-import only** (`waveform-preview.tsx`) |
| Local cache | Dexie.js IndexedDB (`src/lib/sync/cache.ts`) |
| Deploy | Docker (`node:20-slim`), `docker-compose.yml`, optional IIS reverse proxy |

